# FastAPI router paths: avoid APIRouter prefix

Prefer **full URL paths** on each route decorator and use `APIRouter` for `tags` only (and other metadata), not `prefix`.

```python
# ❌ BAD — router prefix hides actual route paths
router = APIRouter(prefix="/posts", tags=["posts"])

@router.post("")
async def create_post(): ...
```

```python
# ✅ GOOD — full paths are explicit
router = APIRouter(tags=["posts"])

@router.post("/posts")
async def create_post(): ...
```
